Changed repo_name logic for bare repos We use a central hook that we symlink to everywhere and were seeing pushes that said "Commit on gitlab-shell (master)", '/gitlab-shell/hooks' being where the hook is stored. pass duration to _text this makes the function signature for `_text()` different from the other
formatting functions used in `notify()`; not sure if that's the lesser evil or
of i should just pass `duration` to every one of those functions.

parametrize other arguments to notify()'s event() call currently, if you want to send in additional information from fabric, there is
no way to do it short of creating your own version of the fab script from the
api. this change enables something like the following:

```python
  def my_tags(t, args, kwargs, error):
    return ["user:%s" % env.user]
  def my_title(t, args, kwargs, error):
    return '%s.%s' % (t.__name__, env.host)

  from dogapi import fab
  fab._tags = my_tags
  fab._title = my_title
```

which makes it possible to customize fabric notification events without
rewriting the entire thing.
refactor fabric notify() this is mainly for DRY and easier reading/following
